What forkers must do
--------------------

Replace the identity layer with your own **before** you use the system in your name:

    bin/identity-init.sh --slug <your-slug> --name "Your Name" --apply

That scaffolds the forker-owned `identity/` surface. It deliberately keeps the
reference prose in place so you can see what to write — which means that until you
overwrite `identity/voice.md`, `identity/operator.md` and `identity/twin-persona.md`,
**you are still running Roberto's persona, not yours.** Finish the rewrite.

