If you deploy an agent built on this system in a way that interacts with third
parties, disclose that they are dealing with an automated system. The upstream canon
holds itself to this rule (`agents/twin.md` § "Delegation, not impersonation", and
the `draft-not-send` guardrail); a fork that removes the rule takes on whatever
obligations apply to it.


